The last time I saw a green scale for sale, 150kpp was asked for it. <br>
<br>
Moreover, you cannot compare rebreathers, an item handmade by gnomes, with a scale from a green dragon.<br>
In one case, you don't have any choice but to buy it (or eventually to make it by yourself, if you're a gnome).<br>
In the other case, you (normally) have to kill the dragon, and take one of his scale as a proof of your action.<br>
<br>
One more time, this isn't an &quot;epic trade&quot;, this is an &quot;epic QUEST&quot;.<br>
I do not find normal to buy a scale from a green dragon like I could buy some milk at a bazaar, I do not find normal to have to kill several time the same dragon that have A LOT of scales in order to be able to get ONE of these, and I do not find normal to take a ticket to kill a dragon like I take a ticket in a butcher's shop.<br>
<br>
Oh, and I'm not only complaining about *my* epic, but also for paladin's and sk's, and even mage's and others classes.<br>
Epics quests aren't balanced, and the current &quot;unbalance&quot; isn't only about risk vs. reward, that was my point. <p><img src="http://perso.wanadoo.fr/mcduck/images/signature.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 11:20:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1264.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ....</span><hr size=1> The Epics quests aren't balanced and neither is anything else in the game.  10 to 20k on a Green scale would be easy to afford, but that was a rarity.  Greens are 75k on Sol Ro, which is only half of Karana, but when you are someone dealing with scraping together cash for any kind of upgrade, digging 75k out to BUY a piece of your Epic from someone who punched a button and melted a dragon down just isn't very epic.  Just as an aside, I think requiring the 2 rebreathers is just stupid too.<br>
<br>
Like I said in another post...<br>
<br>
Fighting deep in to the Plane of Sky...that's epic.  Battling the lieutenants of a God in their home... that's epic.  Wading into the fiery breath of a red dragon to slay it... that's epic.  Invading a city to slay it's Queen... that's epic.  Hoarding cash to buy a dragon scale from a team of wizards who effortlessly blasted a dragon apart in 2 seconds and are holding that scale hostage until someone meets their price... not so epic.<br>
<br>
My deepest conagratualations to any Warrior who had a chance to actually fight for all the parts of their Epic.  I don't think there are many of us want the Epic to be easier, I think that most people would just like a chance to FIGHT for it, not buy it.<br>
